<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="174" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1222,2104,673,863]" pageId="0" pageNumber="174">• Small to medium-sized with relatively thick,silky, long pelage; relatively small eyes; otter-shaped heads and bodies; broad muzzles; flatten nose shields; short ears; and short legs.</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6656770" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6656770" box="[1223,1412,830,863]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6656770/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="174" targetBox="[1256,2071,893,1083]" targetPageId="0">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1222,2104,673,863]" box="[1223,1412,830,863]" pageId="0" pageNumber="174">• 20-60 cm.</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6656772" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6656772" box="[1222,1570,1103,1141]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6656772/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="174" targetBox="[208,1154,674,1298]" targetPageId="0">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1220,2104,893,1305]" box="[1222,1570,1103,1141]" pageId="0" pageNumber="174">• Afrotropical Region.</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="0.[1220,2104,893,1305]" pageId="0" pageNumber="174">• Small rivers and streams in tropical forests up to midelevations mountains.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[1220,2104,893,1305]" box="[1222,1659,1221,1259]" pageId="0" pageNumber="174">• 2 genera, 3 species, 3 taxa.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[1220,2104,893,1305]" box="[1222,1992,1265,1298]" pageId="0" pageNumber="174">• No species threatened; none Extinct since 1600.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
